  "time_ut": 1657343268,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0db7\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dc4 \u0da2\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0d9f\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc5\u0db9\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A flood of people to Colombo to participate in the struggle",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Our reporters say that a large crowd is currently coming to Colombo to participate in the massive protest in Colombo today (9), demanding that the government including President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa should leave immediately.",
        "This struggle has been organized under the theme of 'The whole country to Colombo at 9.00 am on the 9th'",
        "A number of opposition political parties, including the People's Force, have declared their support for this struggle, and a large number of religious leaders, university professors, professionals, artists, and university students, led by the Maha Sangharatne, are currently marching in Colombo.",
        "A large number of people are coming on foot from different areas such as Gampaha, Ragama, Negombo, Kalutara etc. to participate in this struggle.",
        "Its purpose was to inform the people about this struggle and to protest the existing situation, and the people who came near the public library also held a conference there. In addition, a bike ride from Kurunegala to Colombo also started yesterday (7) and it is scheduled to reach Colombo today (9).",
        "In support of the struggle, a protest march organized by the Inter-University Student Union was held from Kelaniya University to Colombo yesterday (8). Many monk organizations have started a trinitarian monk satyagraha at Colombo Fort yesterday (7), and a group of monks have started a continuous fast there, saying that Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa should step down from the presidency.",
        "A large number of religious priests and civil organizations have started a march from Wattala yesterday (7) to join this struggle.",
        "It is also reported that a train is running from Kandy to Colombo and the activists have paid money to reserve the train."
      ],
